text:
You probably won‚Äôt see this gura, but here are some tips!!! üí™üèºüí™üèº

1. You can clean your horse by brushing it. It will be located on the same tab as feeding or petting it (have to be off your horse) You can also get a faster horse at the stables located in valentine or any other place with the stables icon. You can also customize your horse saddle and the horse itself! 
2. You can fast travel! If you look on your map for the directional sign you can use it to fast travel. It‚Äôll be for a fee, depending on how far it is. There‚Äôs one in valentine in front of the train station 
3. The reason you were wanted after not doing anything was because you had a bounty in that area. The people shooting at you were cops. Though, you will run into bounty hunters most of the time which you can kill off. If you have a bounty in a area, be on the look-out for bounty hunters. Who will attack you. 
4. You can pay off your bounty! Go to any icon with the ‚Äúmail‚Äù symbol and you can pay off your bounties there. Which means you won‚Äôt have to deal with the law or bounty hunters unless you commit a crime which brings to tip 5
5. You can commit any crime if you want. Reason you didn‚Äôt get wanted when placing the man on the train tracks was because there was nobody else around. The crime mechanics work with a witness system. You can kill anyone, anywhere if you wanted. (Those random people on horses on the trails and what not). But before you do, make sure there‚Äôs nobody else around. If a person sees you committing a crime you well get a witness bar which will slowly fill up. Failing to kill the witness will result in you getting a wanted bar. 
6. Don‚Äôt worry about the people on the trails. Unless they are marked red on the mini map on the bottom left of your screen. This indicates they are O‚ÄôDriscoll, bounty hunters, cops, or anyone else trying to harm you. This includes animals such as wolfs, bears, mountain lions, snakes, etc. if you see red dot/s on your mini map they aren‚Äôt friendly. 
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
Some good-to-know things! 
1. Arthur can get a haircut and have different beard styles! Go to any icon with the ‚Äúscissors‚Äù iron. There‚Äôs one inside the bar in valentine. 
2. You can buy different weapons and customize them! Go to any ‚Äúgun‚Äù icon. There‚Äôs also one in valentine! 
3. There‚Äôs lots of cool and unique Easter eggs in the game. Like UFOs and such. 
4. Areas on the map labeled with ‚Äú?‚Äù Are areas of interest. Side quests. Side quests will be marked with a white circle. Unlike the main quests, which are marked in yellow. 
5. You can find dinosaur bones scattered on the map! 
6. You can come across a serial killer! (Hint: follow the blood train on the train tracks near valentine 
7. You can go fishing 
8. Use dead eye!!! It‚Äôs really useful. It slows down time, giving you the ability to select multiple enemies in which if you highlighted anyone (preferred on the head for that one shot kill) Arthur will straight up aim bot any selected areas on the enemies
9. You can run up to somebody, tackle them to the ground, and shot them in the head. 

If you guys want to post more tips or good-to-know things bellow, feel free to post them!
